        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2009-08-21T18:39:24Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ Policyholder Disaster Protection Act of 2009 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow insurance companies (other than life insurance companies) to make tax deductible contributions to a tax-exempt policyholder disaster protection fund established by this Act for the payment of policyholders' claims arising from certain catastrophic events, such as windstorms, earthquakes, fires, or floods.]]></text>
      </summary>
